JOHANNESBURG - Research by short-term lender Wonga indicates the country's festive spending is set to increase by 24 percent. South Africans will each spend on average R6,585 in festive expenses, over and above their usual budget, this is R880 more than they spent last year on festivities. READ: Put away some of your December bonus, financial planner urges Wonga's research also reveals 60 percent of people expect to spend more this season than in 2018. Wonga spokesperson Emma King said the majority of people would be purchasing more food and drink for the festivities, likely entertaining, travelling within the country, and buying gifts for friends and family. King said the majority of surveyed people said they would be relying on their end-of-year bonuses to fund the additional expenses.